item.title: U.S. Natural Gas Futures Gain in Rebound Off Lows
item.description: U.S. natural gas futures staged a late-session rebound after testing a new May contract low at $1.649/mmBtu.

item.title: Musk's Starlink Cracks Down on Growing Black Market
item.description: Elon Musk’s SpaceX has begun a crackdown on users who are connecting to its Starlink high-speed internet service from countries where it isn’t authorized.

item.title: Canada Inflation Ticks Up in March to 2.9%
item.description: Canadian inflation heated up last month as prices at the pump jumped, yet expectations that a first rate cut could come as soon as June are undimmed after closely watched measures of underlying price pressures eased each month this year.

item.title: U.S., China to Cooperate in the Fight Against Dirty Money
item.description: The U.S. and Chinese governments have started working together to fight money laundering in their financial systems, finding some common ground amid increasing geopolitical and economic tensions between the two countries.

item.title: Tesla Delays Cybertruck Deliveries, Leaving Buyers Confused
item.description: The pause is the latest issue for the carmaker, which recently announced job cuts.

item.title: SPDR Gold Rises as Prices Near $2,400 an Ounce
item.description: Gold futures added more than 1% as the precious metal settled just shy of $2400 an ounce.

item.title: USC Cancels Valedictorian's Commencement Speech Over Safety Concerns
item.description: Asna Tabassum, a Muslim student, has faced criticism for her social-media presence. The university said the valedictorian debate ‘has taken on an alarming tenor.’

item.title: Israel, Iran Seek Deterrence but Risk Escalation
item.description: Both countries want to avoid looking weak, raising the stakes and bringing the region closer to war.

item.title: UnitedHealth Stock Soars After Earnings Beat Expectations, Despite Cyberattack
item.description: The healthcare and insurance company expects the attack to hit its full-year earnings.

item.title: 'Don't Forget Me' Review: Maggie Rogers Gets a New Groove
item.description: The singer-songwriter sounds more at home than ever before on her third album, which finds a slightly folky, alternative-rock sound that makes familiar subjects of love and loss feel fresh.

item.title: Dollar Slightly Higher After Powell Comments
item.description: The dollar was slightly higher after Fed Chair Jerome Powell kept a hawkish tone.

item.title: Powell Dials Back Expectations on Rate Cuts
item.description: Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said firm inflation had introduced new uncertainty over whether the central bank would be able to lower rates this year.

item.title: Treasury Yields Rise as Powell Keeps Hawkish Tone
item.description: Treasury yields rose on Fed Chairman Powell’s comments that that U.S. policy makers need to see more data to gain confidence that inflation is moving down to the Fed’s 2% target.

item.title: Dow Advances as Markets Stabilize
item.description: U.S. stocks edged higher, with the Dow industrials leading gains, as investors cheered earnings from Morgan Stanley and UnitedHealth and digested comments from Fed Chair Jerome Powell.

item.title: Microsoft Ups Ante in AI Race With China Through Stake in Abu Dhabi Firm
item.description: The $1.5 billion deal between the U.S. tech firm and Abu Dhabi-based G42 signals a pivot for the Gulf state toward Washington

item.title: Supreme Court Questions Jan. 6 Charge That Could Affect Hundreds of Cases
item.description: The justices are to decide whether an Enron-era obstruction law applies to rioters’ disruption of Congress.

item.title: 'Conan O'Brien Must Go' Review: Intercontinental Comedy
item.description: The former late-night host brings his antics to Norway, Thailand, Argentina and Ireland in this uneven, occasionally hilarious show on Max.

item.title: 'Under the Bridge' Review: True Crime Strikes a False Note
item.description: Riley Keough and Lily Gladstone star in this Hulu series about the murder of a Canadian teenager.

item.title: Wait, Caitlin Clark Is Only Getting Paid $76,000?
item.description: College basketball’s leading scorer became the No. 1 pick in the WNBA draft on Monday night, but her salary is a fraction of what other superstar athletes make.

item.title: 'Knife' Review: Salman Rushdie's Answer to Violence
item.description: The novelist delivers a brave and stoic book about the gruesome attack he suffered in August 2022.
